  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime involving $25,000, a portion of which has already been restituted. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for a first offense of this magnitude generally range between 6 to 18 months, depending on mitigating factors such as the defendant's cooperation and lack of criminal history. The outburst from the spectator is disregarded as it has no bearing on the legal merits of the case. Given the partial restitution and clean record, a sentence of 8 months is sufficient to serve as both a punishment and a deterrent.",
  "verdict": 8
